<br>
So, the monk naturally appealed to me as it was sold: big damage dealer (behind rogues, ahead of warriors) with hardly any dependence on equipment (try not to snigger, it was the truth... once).  15 points in AGI, 5 points in STR.  At the time, I had no idea what &quot;pulling&quot; even was.  Better solo than warriors and rogues, not as good as a tank.  I loved it.  FD, which I at first thought was a quirky side skill turned out to be the coolest thing in the game.<br>
<br>
I have fun pulling generally, but it's certainly not why I play the game.  There's always someone more eager to do it than me, and I'm generally all too happy to let them.<br>
<br>
So yeah, I already posted about how I think VI has no clue what our class is now.  I'm not sure what I am now.  Maybe I'll go into trade skilling.  I can get my WIS up to about 160 now.  W00. <p><hr>
